This is taken from the Parliament.uk website;
"We live in a democratic country, which means we all have a say in how the country is run. We do this by electing Members of Parliament (MPs) to REPRESENT OUR VIEWS in the House of Commons." 
Parliament has completely FAILED to represent the will of the British people on the subject of whether the UK should be involved in bombing Syria. All polls conducted in the run up to the parliamentary vote showed the vast majority to be against this action.
